The paper deals with approximation algorithms for graph problems, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of balanced separators and the specific problems studied (chordal graphs, distance hereditary graphs, and minor-closed families) suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to cs.DS and cs.CG, followed by cs.DM, cs.GT, and cs.CC.
